==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Glyoxime
<hw>Gly*ox"ime</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Gly</ets>oxal
+ <ets>oxime</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A white, crystalline,
nitrogenous substance, produced by the action of hydroxylamine on
glyoxal, and belonging to the class of <xex>oximes</xex>; also, any one
of a group of substances resembling glyoxime proper, and of which it is
a type. See <er>Oxime</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glyph</ent>⟦br⟧
